#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code shortest unsorted continuous subarray ka left aur right boundary stack ki help se nikalta hai.

1. Pehle left boundary find karte hain:
   - Left se right traverse karte hain.
   - Stack me indices store hote hain in increasing order.
   - Jab current element stack top se chhota milta hai,
     to matlab sorting yahin se break hui hai.
   - Tab left ko update karte hain.

2. Phir right boundary find karte hain:
   - Right se left traverse karte hain.
   - Is baar stack ki help se check karte hain ki kahaan bada element galat position par hai.
   - Jahan descending issue milta hai, right update hota hai.

3. Agar left >= right ho, to array already sorted hai → answer 0.
4. Warna unsorted subarray ki length = right - left + 1.

Main idea:
Jahaan order break hota hai, wahi actual unsorted region ka part hota hai.
Stack se efficiently first wrong left boundary aur last wrong right boundary mil jaate hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.*;

public class Solution {
    public int findUnsortedSubarray(int[] nums) {
        //You can code here

        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int left = nums.length - 1;
        //Figuring out left
        for(int i=0; i<nums.length;){
          if(stack.isEmpty()){
            stack.push(i);
            i++;
          }
          else{
            //if not empty then check if top element is showing dip
            if(nums[stack.peek()] > nums[i]){
              left = Math.min(left, stack.peek());
              stack.pop();
            }
            else{
              stack.push(i);
              i++;
            }
          }
        }

        //Figuring out right
        int right = 0;
        stack.clear();

        for(int i=nums.length - 1; i>=0;){
          if(stack.isEmpty()){
            stack.push(i);
            i--;
          }
          else{
            if(nums[stack.peek()] < nums[i]){
              right = Math.max(right, stack.peek());
              stack.pop();
            }
            else{
              stack.push(i);
              i--;
            }
          }
        }

        if(left >= right) return 0;
        else{
          return right - left + 1;
        }   
    }
}
